The paper involves the use of Deep Neural Networks (DNN) for image classification, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Gramian Angular Summation Field (GASF) to transform EEG signals into RGB images falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves the diagnosis of epilepsy, which is related to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
